title: Taiwan president denounces China after Honduras breaks off relations with Taiwan
description: In a video address, Taiwan’s President Tsai-Ing Wen said Taiwan will not “engage in dollar diplomacy” with China shortly after Honduras severed relations with Taiwan and established diplomatic ties with China.

title: Hong Kong holds first protest in years under tight restrictions
description: Demonstrators in Hong Kong held a protest against a proposed land reclamation and rubbish processing project under strict rules, the first authorized protest since the lifting of major Covid-19 restrictions.

title: Planets on parade: Five will be lined up in night sky this week
description: Keep an eye to the sky this week for a chance to see a planetary hangout.

title: Hong Kongers hold first protest in years under strict rules
description: Dozens of people on Sunday joined Hong Kong’s first authorized protest since the lifting of major Covid-19 restrictions under unprecedentedly strict rules, including wearing a numbered badge around their necks.

title: A Muslim minority loyal to Ukraine bears the brunt of Russia’s crackdown in Crimea
description: KYIV, Ukraine — The plight of a Muslim minority in Russian-occupied Crimea is highlighting a crackdown in a region that President Vladimir Putin has tried to present as an example of the Kremlin’s right to Ukrainian territory.

title: Honduras forms diplomatic ties with China after breaking relations with Taiwan
description: Honduras formed diplomatic ties with China on Sunday after breaking off relations with Taiwan, which is increasingly isolated and now recognized by only 13 sovereign states, including Vatican City.
